column5: To all of you Chicago folks that have been up to Canada so far this year, what is the word on construction taking 90 out of Chicago, 90/94/39 up to Eau Claire, and then 53 to the border? Sounds like the 502 is in **** shape, but that is normal. Safe travel and tight lines to all!
Three weeks ago we didn't have any problems to Duluth MN. We don't go up 53 or 502 anymore. So that's the best I can do.
